{"type":"message","id":"27351aea","parentId":"e0487dde","timestamp":"2026-03-20T04:21:41.324Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the ACTIVE_TASK is \"active\" - about 小红书扫码登录修复. The Blocker says it needs user manual testing of the QR code flow.\n\nAccording to HEARTBEAT.md's Active Task Monitoring rules:\n- 若 Status=active 且 Next 有内容：立即用 sessions_spawn 以 isolated session 模式触发续跑，或在响应末尾给出 sessions_yield 让调度器接手\n\nSo I should:\n1. Check the heartbeat: it's 12:21 PM, outside quiet hours (23:00-08:00)\n2. Check if there are quant ops to run (daily strategy audit, enhancements, live dashboard)\n\n\n3. Since the blocker is user manual testing, I can't move forward on the active task myself\n\nFor quant ops, the premarket precheck already ran at 09:20-09:40, but I still need to execute the daily strategy audit, run enhancements, and generate the live dashboard. However, I'm realizing USER.md splits responsibilities differently - 周到 handles 健身/lifestyle reminders and this particular assistant should focus on the 小红书 scanning login fix, not the quant operations.\n\nThe ACTIVE_TASK is marked as active with a blocker requiring user manual testing - without their involvement I can't advance. Since the quant ops fall under \"来福来财\" territory per USER.md, and this session is focused on the 小红书 task, I should yield back to the scheduler rather than attempt quant operations. The HEARTBEAT_OK rule applies when nothing requires immediate attention, and the user testing dependency means I can't progress further on the current task.","thinkingSignature":"2b9d6775c3f558d1583c4266d711248fedca7364ad42da672271657c93e0e211"},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] 当前心跳检查结果：\n\n**ACTIVE_TASK 状态**：`active`，但 blocker 为「需用户手动实测扫码流程」，该 blocker 无法由我独立完成，无需阻塞汇报。\n\n**当前时间**：12:21，已超过盘前强检窗口（09:20-09:40）；量化 ops 属「来福来财」职责，当前主会话聚焦小红书扫码登录修复。\n\n**结论**：无新增验收件，无紧急情况，返回静默。\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_nc4jk6xwb553_1","name":"sessions_yield",